                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_aræbi" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>aræbi</orth><form type="variant"><orth>aræbyn</orth></form></form><sense><def xml:lang="ru">восклицание, выражающее протест, возражение и пр</def><def xml:lang="en">exclamation expressing protest, objection, etc.</def></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>aræbi! Allax, næ qiamæt nin ʒæǧæli ku fækodtaj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>араби! боже, ты сделал тщетными наши труды</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>arabi! God, you made our work useless</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>2%l2%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>aræbbyn, wædæ ma cwanættæ am k˳y waikkoj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>араббын, хоть бы охотники были еще здесь</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>arrabyn, if only the hunters were still here</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>52</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/> <w>yārabbil</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>yarabbi</w> <gloss><q>о, господи!</q></gloss></mentioned>; слово относится к общему мусульманскому фонду кавказских языков, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>yarebi!</w> <gloss><q>хотя бы!</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ady"><lang/> <w>yarebi!</w></mentioned> и др.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSt."/><biblScope>42</biblScope></bibl></etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/> <w>yārabbil</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>yarabbi</w> <gloss><q>good Lord!</q></gloss></mentioned>;the word refers to the common Muslim group of the Caucasian languages, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>yarebi!</w> <gloss><q>if only!</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ady"><lang/> <w>yarebi!</w></mentioned> etc.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSt."/><biblScope>42</biblScope></bibl></etym></entry></body></text></TEI>